{"id":"int-ed0b9ac6","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-03-27T06:02:14.369747Z","actor":"mistakeknot","issue_id":"sylveste-m0m","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"open","reason":"NEGATIVE RESULT: Polar coordinate KV cache quantization does NOT work. Three iterations: (1) Original wrapper called inverse_polar_transform on quantized tuples — structurally broken. (2) Fixed dequantize-then-inverse with interleaved layout — 3.1x worse error. (3) Contiguous r/theta layout — 1.19x worse at 4-bit, still garbage output at ALL bit widths (2,4,8). Root cause: inverse trig transform amplifies quantization noise by 2.7x — angle error delta_theta becomes Cartesian error r*sin(delta_theta), proportional to radius. High-radius vectors (most important for attention) suffer most. This is a fundamental mathematical limitation. Kept code for reference."}}
